  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith spot at 6600.95 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6609 and massive positive gamma walls at 6605 (+12.6B) and 6600 (+10.0B), dealers are likely selling rallies aggressively to hedge their long gamma positions. The recent wall break and GEX surge events indicate heightened volatility, but the PIN regime suggests dealers will continue providing liquidity by fading moves - selling any push toward 6605-6610 and buying weakness toward 6500. Key levels to monitor are the 6605 max gamma strike above (heavy selling pressure) and 6500 below where negative gamma flips dealers into amplifying mode.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action with upside capped near 6605 and support building around 6600.",
